Import Data

In this project, I want to build an interpretable, clinically valid supervised ML model that predicts in-hospital mortality for critically ill patients in the SUPPORT2 dataset using day-3 demographic, diagnostic, physiologic, and lab features with robust handling of missingness and non-IID structure.

# I excluded features with more than 50% missing values to avoid 
# imputation-driven noise and keep the pipeline simple and robust.
# I also removed post-outcome and downstream variables 
# (e.g., charges, LOS, modelled survival) to prevent information 
# leakage and preserve clinical validity.

target = "hospdead"
y = df[target].astype(int)

drop_cols = [
    "Index", "charges", "totcst", "totmcst",

Data Preprocessing

In[5]:
# Categorical: impute + OneHot Encoder
categorical_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("imputer", SimpleImputer(strategy="constant", fill_value="missing")),
    ("onehot",  OneHotEncoder(sparse_output=False, handle_unknown="ignore"))
])

# Ordinal: impute + Ordinal Encoder
ordinal_str_cats = [
    ["under $11k", "$11-$25k", "$25-$50k", ">$50k", "missing"],
    ["no", "yes", "metastatic", "missing"]
]
ordinal_str_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("imputer", SimpleImputer(strategy="constant", fill_value="missing")),
    ("ordinal", OrdinalEncoder(categories=ordinal_str_cats))
])

ordinal_num_cats = [
    [0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8],  # 8 represents missing
    [0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8]
]
ordinal_num_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("imputer", SimpleImputer(strategy="constant", fill_value=8)),
    ("ordinal", OrdinalEncoder(categories=ordinal_num_cats))
])

from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# continuous
numeric_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("scaler", StandardScaler())
])

preprocessor_reduced = ColumnTransformer(
    transformers=[
        ("cat",      categorical_transformer, categorical_ftrs),
        ("ord_str",  ordinal_str_transformer, ordinal_str_ftrs),
        ("ord_num",  ordinal_num_transformer, ordinal_num_ftrs),
        ("num",      numeric_transformer,     continuous_ftrs),
    ],
    remainder="drop"
)

Model Training

In[6]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.base import clone
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier

from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score

# ---------------------------
#  missingness pattern 
# ---------------------------

def pattern_reduced_model(model, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test):
    """
     base model( LogisticRegression / LinearSVC / RandomForestClassifier),
     continuous missingness pattern  X_test 
     y_test  pd.Series /score( NaN, AUC  mask 
    """

    # 1)  + fit on train
    X_train_enc = pd.DataFrame(
        preprocessor_reduced.fit_transform(X_train),
        index=X_train.index
    )
    X_val_enc = pd.DataFrame(
        preprocessor_reduced.transform(X_val),
        index=X_val.index
    )
    X_test_enc = pd.DataFrame(
        preprocessor_reduced.transform(X_test),
        index=X_test.index
    )

    #  len(continuous_ftrs) 
    cont_start = X_train_enc.shape[1] - len(continuous_ftrs)
    cont_cols  = list(X_train_enc.columns[cont_start:])

    # 2)  test  pattern
    mask = X_test_enc[cont_cols].isna()
    patterns = np.unique(mask.to_numpy(), axis=0)

    out_pred = pd.Series(index=y_test.index, dtype=float)

    for pattern in patterns:
        #  pattern  test 
        pattern_rows = mask.apply(lambda row: np.array_equal(row.values, pattern), axis=1)
        if not pattern_rows.any():
            continue

        X_test_sub = X_test_enc.loc[pattern_rows]
        y_test_sub = y_test.loc[pattern_rows]

        #  pattern  continuous  -> 
        cont_cols_to_keep = [c for c, keep in zip(cont_cols, ~pattern) if keep]
        usable_cols = list(X_train_enc.columns[:cont_start]) + cont_cols_to_keep

        #  /  NaN reduced-features
        X_train_sub = X_train_enc[usable_cols].dropna()
        y_train_sub = y_train.loc[X_train_sub.index]

        X_val_sub = X_val_enc[usable_cols].dropna()
        y_val_sub = y_val.loc[X_val_sub.index]

        if (len(X_train_sub) == 0) or (len(X_test_sub) == 0):
            continue

        #  pattern 
        mdl = clone(model).fit(X_train_sub, y_train_sub)

        if hasattr(mdl, "predict_proba"):
            pred = mdl.predict_proba(X_test_sub[usable_cols])[:, 1]
        else:
            # LinearSVC  decision_function
            pred = mdl.decision_function(X_test_sub[usable_cols])

        out_pred.loc[X_test_sub.index] = pred

    return out_pred

#  loop 
def run_LR(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test):
    mdl = LogisticRegression(max_iter=3000, solver="liblinear", **params)
    return pattern_reduced_model(mdl, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)

def run_SVM(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test):
    mdl = LinearSVC(**params)
    return pattern_reduced_model(mdl, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)

def run_RF(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test):
    mdl = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=0, n_jobs=-1, **params)
    return pattern_reduced_model(mdl, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)

In[18]:
def tune_pattern_model(model_name, param_grid,
                       X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test):
    """
     grid-search:
    -  (train, val)  pattern_reduced_model;
    -  val AUC 
    -  test  AUC
    """
    # param_grid  dict
    if not param_grid:
        params = {}
        if model_name == "LR":
            pred_test = run_LR(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
        elif model_name == "SVM":
            pred_test = run_SVM(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
        elif model_name == "RF":
            pred_test = run_RF(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
        mask = ~pred_test.isna()
        test_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test[mask], pred_test[mask])
        return params, test_auc

    best_params = None
    best_val_auc = -np.inf
    best_test_pred = None

    keys = list(param_grid.keys())
    for values in product(*param_grid.values()):
        params = dict(zip(keys, values))

        if model_name == "LR":
            pred_val = run_LR(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_val, y_val)
        elif model_name == "SVM":
            pred_val = run_SVM(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_val, y_val)
        elif model_name == "RF":
            pred_val = run_RF(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_val, y_val)
        else:
            raise ValueError(f"Unknown model: {model_name}")

        mask_val = ~pred_val.isna()
        val_auc = roc_auc_score(y_val[mask_val], pred_val[mask_val])

        if val_auc > best_val_auc:
            best_val_auc = val_auc
            best_params = params

            #  test 
            if model_name == "LR":
                best_test_pred = run_LR(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
            elif model_name == "SVM":
                best_test_pred = run_SVM(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
            elif model_name == "RF":
                best_test_pred = run_RF(params, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)

    mask_test = ~best_test_pred.isna()
    test_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test[mask_test], best_test_pred[mask_test])
    return best_params, test_auc

from collections import defaultdict
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, accuracy_score, f1_score
import numpy as np

#  metric
metrics = ["auc", "acc", "f1"]

#  1  baseline + 4 
model_names = ["baseline", "LR", "SVM", "RF", "XGB"]

# results[model][metric] = [metric over seeds]
results = {
    m: {metric: [] for metric in metrics}
    for m in model_names
}

seeds = range(5)   #  0,1,2,3,4

for rs in seeds:
    print(f"\n=========================")
    print(f" Random State = {rs}")
    print(f"=========================")

    # 1)  other / test
    X_other, X_test, y_other, y_test = train_test_split(
        X, y,
        test_size=0.2,
        random_state=rs,
        stratify=y
    )

    #  other  train / valpattern 
    X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(
        X_other, y_other,
        test_size=0.25,   # -> 0.6 train, 0.2 val, 0.2 test
        random_state=rs,
        stratify=y_other
    )

    # ------------------------------------------------
    #  baseline
    # ------------------------------------------------
    majority_class = y_train.value_counts().idxmax()

    # baseline  test 
    baseline_pred_label = np.full_like(y_test, fill_value=majority_class)

    # AUC score
    baseline_score_auc = np.full_like(
        y_test,
        fill_value=y_train.mean(),
        dtype=float
    )

    baseline_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, baseline_score_auc)
    baseline_acc = accuracy_score(y_test, baseline_pred_label)
    baseline_f1  = f1_score(y_test, baseline_pred_label, zero_division=0)

    print(f"Baseline (majority) on test:")
    print(f"  AUC = {baseline_auc:.4f}, "
          f"Accuracy = {baseline_acc:.4f}, "
          f"F1 = {baseline_f1:.44f}")

    results["baseline"]["auc"].append(baseline_auc)
    results["baseline"]["acc"].append(baseline_acc)
    results["baseline"]["f1"].append(baseline_f1)

    # ------------------------------------------------
    # Reduced-feature models: LR / SVM / RF
    # ------------------------------------------------
    # LR
    print(f"\nTuning LR (pattern-reduced)...")
    best_params_lr, _ = tune_pattern_model(
        "LR",
        param_grids["LR"],
        X_train, y_train,
        X_val,   y_val,
        X_test,  y_test
    )
    print(f"Best params for LR: {best_params_lr}")

    #  best_params  test score 
    lr_scores = run_LR(best_params_lr, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
    mask_lr   = ~lr_scores.isna()

    lr_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test[mask_lr], lr_scores[mask_lr])
    lr_pred_label = (lr_scores >= 0.5).astype(int)
    lr_acc = accuracy_score(y_test[mask_lr], lr_pred_label[mask_lr])
    lr_f1  = f1_score(y_test[mask_lr], lr_pred_label[mask_lr])

    print(f"LR on test:")
    print(f"  AUC = {lr_auc:.4f}, Accuracy = {lr_acc:.4f}, F1 = {lr_f1:.4f}")

    results["LR"]["auc"].append(lr_auc)
    results["LR"]["acc"].append(lr_acc)
    results["LR"]["f1"].append(lr_f1)

    # SVM
    print(f"\nTuning SVM (pattern-reduced)...")
    best_params_svm, _ = tune_pattern_model(
        "SVM",
        param_grids["SVM"],
        X_train, y_train,
        X_val,   y_val,
        X_test,  y_test
    )
    print(f"Best params for SVM: {best_params_svm}")

    svm_scores = run_SVM(best_params_svm, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
    mask_svm   = ~svm_scores.isna()

    svm_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test[mask_svm], svm_scores[mask_svm])
    # LinearSVC: decision_function >= 0 
    svm_pred_label = (svm_scores >= 0).astype(int)
    svm_acc = accuracy_score(y_test[mask_svm], svm_pred_label[mask_svm])
    svm_f1  = f1_score(y_test[mask_svm], svm_pred_label[mask_svm])

    print(f"SVM on test:")
    print(f"  AUC = {svm_auc:.4f}, Accuracy = {svm_acc:.4f}, F1 = {svm_f1:.4f}")

    results["SVM"]["auc"].append(svm_auc)
    results["SVM"]["acc"].append(svm_acc)
    results["SVM"]["f1"].append(svm_f1)

    # RF
    print(f"\nTuning RF (pattern-reduced)...")
    best_params_rf, _ = tune_pattern_model(
        "RF",
        param_grids["RF"],
        X_train, y_train,
        X_val,   y_val,
        X_test,  y_test
    )
    print(f"Best params for RF: {best_params_rf}")

    rf_scores = run_RF(best_params_rf, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val, X_test, y_test)
    mask_rf   = ~rf_scores.isna()

    rf_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test[mask_rf], rf_scores[mask_rf])
    rf_pred_label = (rf_scores >= 0.5).astype(int)
    rf_acc = accuracy_score(y_test[mask_rf], rf_pred_label[mask_rf])
    rf_f1  = f1_score(y_test[mask_rf], rf_pred_label[mask_rf])

    print(f"RF on test:")
    print(f"  AUC = {rf_auc:.4f}, Accuracy = {rf_acc:.4f}, F1 = {rf_f1:.4f}")

    results["RF"]["auc"].append(rf_auc)
    results["RF"]["acc"].append(rf_acc)
    results["RF"]["f1"].append(rf_f1)

    # ------------------------------------------------
    # XGBoost GridSearchCVscoring='roc_auc'
    # ------------------------------------------------
    print("\nTuning XGBoost with GridSearchCV...")

    # XGBoost  preprocessor_reduced 
    X_other_enc = preprocessor_reduced.fit_transform(X_other)
    X_test_enc  = preprocessor_reduced.transform(X_test)

    xgb_base = XGBClassifier(
        tree_method="hist",
        eval_metric="logloss",
        missing=np.nan,
        n_jobs=-1,
        random_state=rs,
    )

    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=rs)

    grid_search = GridSearchCV(
        estimator=xgb_base,
        param_grid=param_grids["XGB"],
        cv=kf,
        scoring="roc_auc",
        return_train_score=True,
        n_jobs=-1,
        verbose=1
    )

    grid_search.fit(X_other_enc, y_other)

    best_xgb        = grid_search.best_estimator_
    best_xgb_params = grid_search.best_params_

    # test 
    xgb_prob = best_xgb.predict_proba(X_test_enc)[:, 1]
    xgb_pred_label = (xgb_prob >= 0.5).astype(int)

    xgb_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, xgb_prob)
    xgb_acc = accuracy_score(y_test, xgb_pred_label)
    xgb_f1  = f1_score(y_test, xgb_pred_label)

    print(f"Best parameters for XGB: {best_xgb_params}")
    print(f"XGB on test:")
    print(f"  AUC = {xgb_auc:.4f}, Accuracy = {xgb_acc:.4f}, F1 = {xgb_f1:.4f}")

    results["XGB"]["auc"].append(xgb_auc)
    results["XGB"]["acc"].append(xgb_acc)
    results["XGB"]["f1"].append(xgb_f1)

    diff = model_auc_arr - base_auc_arr       #  split  baseline 
    mean_diff = diff.mean()
    std_diff  = diff.std()

    if std_diff > 0:
        z = mean_diff / std_diff
    else:
        z = np.nan

    print(f"{model}: mean AUC = {mean_diff:.4f} "
          f"({z:.2f} standard deviations above baseline)")

def get_xgb_importance_df(xgb_model, feature_names, importance_type="gain"):
    """
     XGBClassifier  importance_type,
     importance  DataFrame
    """
    booster = xgb_model.get_booster()
    score_dict = booster.get_score(importance_type=importance_type)  # {'f0': val, 'f12': val, ...}

    rows = []
    for f_id, score in score_dict.items():
        # f_id  'f0', 'f12'
        idx = int(f_id[1:])
        if idx < len(feature_names):
            rows.append({
                "feature": feature_names[idx],
                "importance": score
            })

    df = pd.DataFrame(rows)
    if df.empty:
        print(f"[Warning] No features found for importance_type='{importance_type}'")
        return df.sort_values("importance", ascending=False)

    return df.sort_values("importance", ascending=False)

importance_types = ["weight", "gain", "cover", "total_gain", "total_cover"]
top_k = 10

for imp_type in importance_types:
    fi_df = get_xgb_importance_df(xgb_best, feature_names, importance_type=imp_type)
    print(f"\nTop {top_k} features by XGB {imp_type}:")
    print(fi_df.head(top_k))

    # 
    top_df = fi_df.head(top_k)

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, max(4, 0.3 * len(top_df))))
    plt.barh(top_df["feature"], top_df["importance"])
    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
    plt.xlabel(f"XGBoost importance ({imp_type})")
    plt.title(f"XGBoost feature importance ({imp_type}, top {top_k})")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(f"/Users/norazhou/Desktop/DATA1030/Project/Final_project/figure/xgb_importance_{imp_type}.png",
                dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
    plt.show()

from copy import deepcopy

# baseline test AUC
baseline_auc = roc_auc_score(
    y_test_final,
    xgb_best.predict_proba(X_test_enc)[:, 1]
)
print(f"Baseline test AUC (no shuffle): {baseline_auc:.4f}")

n_features = X_test_enc.shape[1]
n_repeats = 20

perm_auc = np.zeros((n_features, n_repeats))

for j in range(n_features):
    print(f"Shuffling feature: {feature_names[j]}")
    for r in range(n_repeats):
        X_perm = deepcopy(X_test_enc)
        #  j  permute 
        X_perm[:, j] = np.random.permutation(X_perm[:, j])

        y_pred_perm = xgb_best.predict_proba(X_perm)[:, 1]
        perm_auc[j, r] = roc_auc_score(y_test_final, y_pred_perm)

    print("   Shuffled test AUC: %.4f  %.4f"
          % (perm_auc[j].mean(), perm_auc[j].std()))

# AUC 
perm_importance = baseline_auc - perm_auc.mean(axis=1)

fi_perm_df = pd.DataFrame({
    "feature": feature_names,
    "perm_importance_auc_drop": perm_importance
}).sort_values("perm_importance_auc_drop", ascending=False)

print("\nTop permutation importances (AUC drop):")
print(fi_perm_df.head(20))

#  1top20  AUC drop 
top_k = 20
top_perm = fi_perm_df.head(top_k)

plt.figure(figsize=(6, max(4, 0.3 * len(top_perm))))
plt.barh(top_perm["feature"], top_perm["perm_importance_auc_drop"])
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
plt.xlabel("AUC drop after shuffling")
plt.title(f"Permutation feature importance (top {top_k})")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("/Users/norazhou/Desktop/DATA1030/Project/Final_project/figure/xgb_permutation_importance_auc_drop.png",
            dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
plt.show()

#  2 PS10  topk  boxplot permuted AUC 
sorted_idx = np.argsort(perm_importance)[::-1]
top_idx = sorted_idx[:top_k]

plt.rcParams.update({"font.size": 9})
plt.figure(figsize=(8, max(4, 0.3 * len(top_idx))))
plt.boxplot(
    perm_auc[top_idx].T,
    labels=feature_names[top_idx],
    vert=False
)
plt.axvline(baseline_auc, linestyle="--", label="Baseline AUC (no shuffle)")
plt.xlabel("Test AUC after shuffling")
plt.title("Permutation importances (AUC) on test set")

import shap
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def generate_shap_force_plot_png(xgb_model, explainer, shap_values, X_test_enc, feature_names,
                                 index=0,
                                 save_path="/Users/norazhou/Desktop/DATA1030/Project/Final_project/figure/xgb_shap_force_example.png"):
    """
     local SHAP force plot, PNG 
    index: X_test_enc  (iloc)
    """

    shap.initjs()
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 4))  # force plot 

    shap.force_plot(
        explainer.expected_value,
        shap_values[index, :],
        np.round(X_test_enc[index, :], 4),
        feature_names=feature_names,
        matplotlib=True  #   matplotlib 
    )

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
    plt.close()

    print(f"SHAP force plot saved as image: {save_path}")


idx_to_explain = 1

generate_shap_force_plot_png(
    xgb_best,
    explainer,

    X_test_enc,
    feature_names,
    index=idx_to_explain,
    save_path=f"/Users/norazhou/Desktop/DATA1030/Project/Final_project/figure/xgb_shap_force_{idx_to_explain}.png"
)
